    "notes": "Published J Womens Health Phys Ther. 2017;41(2):102-125. Joint CPG from the Section on Women's Health (SOWH) and Orthopaedic Section, American Physical Therapy Association. Covers examination, classification, prognosis, and intervention for pelvic girdle pain (PGP) in the antepartum (pregnant) population. Literature search through 2012. Key examination tests include Active Straight Leg Raise (ASLR), thigh thrust, Gaenslen test, posterior pelvic pain provocation test (P4/thigh thrust), compression/distraction tests."
